WEBVTT



00:00:01.600 --> 00:00:04.416
Oh, hello friends. How are you this morning?

00:00:04.384 --> 00:00:07.552
I had some time and I chose to

00:00:07.392 --> 00:00:09.728
Do some reading in my new book.

00:00:10.240 --> 00:00:13.344
Now time, that's an interesting topic.

00:00:14.112 --> 00:00:16.992
God cares about what we do with our time.

00:00:17.248 --> 00:00:20.128
We probably don't think about time that often.

00:00:20.352 --> 00:00:24.416
But time is one of the many gifts that God has given us.

00:00:24.960 --> 00:00:28.512
Some of our time is used in things that we just do.

00:00:28.288 --> 00:00:30.336
Automatically things that

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:34.080
Our habits maybe like brushing our teeth or

00:00:34.240 --> 00:00:37.024
Putting our pajamas on before we get in bed.

00:00:37.600 --> 00:00:40.832
A lot of our time we get to choose what we want to do.

00:00:40.960 --> 00:00:44.736
Like, I had a choice for a few minutes here whether to

00:00:44.832 --> 00:00:47.264
I'll read some of my book.

00:00:47.456 --> 00:00:48.704
or maybe

00:00:48.576 --> 00:00:50.688
Work on my next lesson

00:00:51.840 --> 00:00:56.320
It's important to God that we use our time in a way that is helpful.

00:00:56.096 --> 00:00:57.472
To ourselves,

00:00:57.408 --> 00:00:58.528
To others

00:00:58.560 --> 00:01:01.568
And it shows that we love Jesus.

00:01:02.080 --> 00:01:04.320
We want to use our time in a way.

00:01:04.544 --> 00:01:05.920
That is helpful.

00:01:06.880 --> 00:01:07.904
You know,

00:01:07.712 --> 00:01:11.744
I have a video that can explain a little bit more about

00:01:11.648 --> 00:01:14.272
Habits and about using our time.

00:01:14.464 --> 00:01:18.528
But before we get to the video, I have a brand new worship song for you.

00:01:18.368 --> 00:01:21.472
It's by a group that I really enjoy.

00:01:21.216 --> 00:01:22.720
Called goldfish.

00:01:23.104 --> 00:01:25.632
So let's do our praise and worship together.

00:01:25.472 --> 00:01:27.456
And then see this video

00:01:27.456 --> 00:01:29.632
About habits and time

00:01:29.600 --> 00:01:31.904
And i'll meet you right back here in a few

00:01:33.344 --> 00:01:39.200
My God is so big and so strong and so mighty, there's nothing my God can do.

00:05:06.400 --> 00:05:10.912
Kids, today we're starting a new series on habits. Do you know what a habit is?

00:05:11.296 --> 00:05:15.104
A habit is something you do over and over again.

00:05:15.904 --> 00:05:25.952
When you get into a habit, you do it without thinking about it. Habits can be good or bad, and it's important to think about them. Make sure you're only doing the good ones. And here's the thing.

00:05:25.472 --> 00:05:26.560
And here's why.

00:05:26.912 --> 00:05:29.536
Habits have a way of controlling us.

00:05:30.464 --> 00:05:33.888
It's like a robot with a fancy control panel.

00:05:33.664 --> 00:05:38.912
When you get into a habit, it's like someone is programming that habit into your system.

00:05:38.688 --> 00:05:41.632
Once it gets in there, it's hard to get it out.

00:05:41.408 --> 00:05:45.440
In this lesson, we want you to think about what's in your program.

00:05:45.184 --> 00:05:48.288
Answer these questions with your parents.

00:05:48.672 --> 00:05:51.488
What are some things that you do every day?

00:05:51.584 --> 00:05:54.464
Are those things good or bad for you?

00:05:54.400 --> 00:05:56.896
What are some other bad habits you have?

00:05:57.376 --> 00:06:02.432
Understanding the habits that you already have will help you decide which ones are good and bad.

00:06:02.848 --> 00:06:07.360
Good habits are things to make your parents and God proud.

00:06:07.776 --> 00:06:12.416
These are the things in your program that are good and helpful things like

00:06:12.224 --> 00:06:13.664
Hoping at home.

00:06:13.568 --> 00:06:14.976
Doing your homework.

00:06:14.976 --> 00:06:17.344
Reading your Bible and praying

00:06:17.344 --> 00:06:20.512
You can add more to this list at home with your parents.

00:06:21.184 --> 00:06:25.696
Bad habits are the things that make your parents and God sad.

00:06:26.144 --> 00:06:31.648
Bad habits come in all shapes and sizes. You've got your gross habits.

00:06:31.392 --> 00:06:33.568
Like chewing your nails

00:06:33.536 --> 00:06:35.264
Picking your nose

00:06:35.104 --> 00:06:37.280
burping really loud

00:06:37.088 --> 00:06:41.376
These are the kinds of things that your mom really doesn't like.

00:06:41.248 --> 00:06:45.120
And then you've got your sin habits. Things like...

00:06:44.896 --> 00:06:48.768
Disobeying your parents? Being mean to other kids?

00:06:48.608 --> 00:06:51.072
Sneaking things without permission?

00:06:50.784 --> 00:06:54.592
These are the kinds of things that God really doesn't like.

00:06:54.432 --> 00:06:55.936
But here's the thing.

00:06:55.808 --> 00:06:58.080
Everyone has bad habits

00:06:57.600 --> 00:06:58.208
8.

00:06:58.400 --> 00:07:02.944
I don't really understand myself, for I want to do what was right.

00:07:02.560 --> 00:07:04.544
But I don't do it.

00:07:04.448 --> 00:07:06.752
Instead, I do what I hate.

00:07:07.200 --> 00:07:11.680
So, how can you change your bad habits but keep your good habits?

00:07:11.488 --> 00:07:13.216
That's a great question.

00:07:13.024 --> 00:07:15.872
And it's what we'll be talking about in this series.

00:07:15.616 --> 00:07:18.464
Do you want to get a sneak peek at the answer right now?

00:07:18.400 --> 00:07:23.840
God will help you. He has the power to reprogram your habits and He really wants to do it.

00:07:23.584 --> 00:07:26.592
Stay tuned and find out how!

00:07:30.336 --> 00:07:35.328
Wow, I really love that song. That's one of my favorite songs that Go Fish does.

00:07:35.168 --> 00:07:36.864
I hope you enjoyed it.

00:07:36.800 --> 00:07:38.688
We're going to be doing that song.

00:07:38.464 --> 00:07:40.160
The whole month of June.

00:07:40.672 --> 00:07:41.728
So,

00:07:41.536 --> 00:07:42.624
Time.

00:07:43.072 --> 00:07:45.440
God cares about how we use our time.

00:07:45.600 --> 00:07:48.640
God gives all of us the same amount of time every day.

00:07:48.416 --> 00:07:49.920
24 hours.

00:07:50.432 --> 00:07:52.608
Now how we use our time

00:07:52.512 --> 00:07:54.464
Is very different from one another.

00:07:55.488 --> 00:07:59.648
Especially the time that we have that we can choose what we want to do.

00:08:00.288 --> 00:08:04.704
Now habits like we talked about are things we kind of do automatically while thinking about it.

00:08:05.056 --> 00:08:07.904
Sometimes the habits are good like brushing your teeth

00:08:08.448 --> 00:08:11.584
Some of the habits are are not so good like

00:08:11.776 --> 00:08:13.216
Skipping,

00:08:13.120 --> 00:08:15.104
Cleaning our room.

00:08:15.584 --> 00:08:20.032
Once a week even though we have said that's what we were going to do.

00:08:20.832 --> 00:08:22.048
You know...

00:08:21.984 --> 00:08:23.712
Using our time

00:08:24.704 --> 00:08:25.856
Shows

00:08:25.984 --> 00:08:27.392
What we care about.

00:08:27.712 --> 00:08:30.400
What we use our time for shows what we care about.

00:08:30.560 --> 00:08:32.608
Do we care more about us?

00:08:32.512 --> 00:08:34.688
Or do we care more about other people?

00:08:34.944 --> 00:08:38.656
And do we care more about showing people that we love Jesus?

00:08:39.008 --> 00:08:44.800
for example, let's say your mother spent all day at work, she came home and made you a really great dinner.

00:08:45.440 --> 00:08:50.240
You could choose to use your time after dinner to help her clean the kitchen.

00:08:50.976 --> 00:08:55.264
Or you could go back to your video game that you were playing all afternoon.

00:08:56.320 --> 00:09:00.192
Or you could choose to read your younger brother's story.

00:09:01.024 --> 00:09:02.464
bedtime story.

00:09:03.712 --> 00:09:04.800
Or...

00:09:04.864 --> 00:09:07.680
you could go watch a television program.

00:09:08.608 --> 00:09:11.936
How we use our time shows what's important to us.

00:09:12.128 --> 00:09:17.952
and if our family and our friends and most of all Jesus are important to us, we're going to use our time

00:09:19.424 --> 00:09:20.704
To show

00:09:20.768 --> 00:09:22.784
That that's what's important to us.

00:09:23.552 --> 00:09:25.344
I have a question for you.

00:09:25.600 --> 00:09:28.224
How can you use your time

00:09:28.096 --> 00:09:30.144
So that you are more helpful

00:09:30.432 --> 00:09:31.840
And it shows

00:09:31.584 --> 00:09:33.184
That you love Jesus.

00:09:34.080 --> 00:09:37.056
This is a question you and your family can discuss.

00:09:38.432 --> 00:09:41.312
Again, how can we use our time

00:09:41.568 --> 00:09:43.648
Just be more helpful

00:09:44.192 --> 00:09:46.208
And show that we love Jesus.

00:09:46.688 --> 00:09:49.568
I hope you'll take time to discuss this with

00:09:49.344 --> 00:09:51.264
Whoever's in the room with you right now,

00:09:51.776 --> 00:09:54.496
I thank you for coming and joining me today.

00:09:54.784 --> 00:09:56.032
And I hope

00:09:56.000 --> 00:09:59.872
That you use your time wisely the rest of this day

00:10:00.256 --> 00:10:02.496
And until I see you again next week.

00:10:02.912 --> 00:10:07.360
Also, don't forget that on Thursdays at 11:00 a.m. on Salem Fields,

00:10:07.808 --> 00:10:10.176
Community church family live

00:10:10.304 --> 00:10:12.256
We do a program.

00:10:12.224 --> 00:10:13.248
For you.

00:10:13.120 --> 00:10:17.024
We do activities and fun things that you can join in with us.

00:10:17.088 --> 00:10:19.456
Or you can watch the video and do it later.

00:10:19.776 --> 00:10:21.216
Thank you so much.

00:10:21.152 --> 00:10:23.328
I hope to see you again next week.

00:10:23.200 --> 00:10:24.192
Bye.
